Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto a
large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @dried oregano{},
season with @salt and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees), halving any large ones.

Pop the broccoli onto another large baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{},
season with @salt and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat.

When the potatoes have roasted for ~{15-20%minutes}, pop the broccoli onto the
middle shelf of the oven.

Roast until the edges are crispy and slightly charred, ~{10-15%minutes}.

When the potatoes have 10 mins remaining, melt the @butter{30%g} (see pantry
for amount) in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of
@oil{}.

Pat the @salmon fillets{2} dry with #kitchen paper{}. Season with @salt and
@ground black pepper{}, then sprinkle over the @lemon & herb seasoning{}.

Once hot, carefully place your salmon into the pan, skin-side down. Cook for
~{3-4%minutes} before turning over and cooking for ~{2-3%minutes} on the other
side.

> TIP: To get crispy skin on the fish, don't move it around when it's cooking
> skin-side down.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Stir the garlic into the melted butter.

Spoon the garlic butter over the fish for ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the
heat.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

When ready, plate up your salmon with the roasted broccoli and potatoes
alongside.

Spoon the remaining garlic butter from the pan over the fish to finish.

Enjoy!